@startuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #E8F4F8
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #FFE6CC

title SD-06 - Admin Login Flow

actor Administrator
participant Browser
participant Server
participant Router
participant Controller
participant Model
database Database

Administrator -> Browser: 1. Navigate to admin login\nGET /administrator
activate Browser

Browser -> Server: 2. GET /administrator
activate Server
deactivate Browser

Server -> Router: 3. Route to Administrator controller
activate Router
deactivate Server

Router -> Controller: 4. Call index() method
activate Controller
deactivate Router

note right of Controller
    Setup login form:
    - Generate captcha
    - Load login template
    - Check for existing session
end note

Controller -> Browser: 5. Render login template\n(template().'/administrator/login', $data)
activate Browser

Browser -> Administrator: 6. Display login form\nwith captcha
deactivate Browser

Administrator -> Browser: 7. Enter credentials and submit\nPOST /administrator/index
activate Browser

Browser -> Server: 8. POST /administrator/index\n(username, password, captcha)
activate Server
deactivate Browser

Server -> Router: 9. Route to Administrator controller index()
activate Router
deactivate Server

Router -> Controller: 10. Call index() method (POST)
activate Controller
deactivate Router

note right of Controller
    Validate form submission:
    - Check required fields
    - Verify captcha
    - Hash password with MD5
end note

Controller -> Model: 11. login($username, md5($password))
activate Model

Model -> Database: 12. SELECT * FROM users\nWHERE username = '$username'\nAND password = MD5('$password')
activate Database
deactivate Model

Database --> Model: 13. Return user data or empty
deactivate Database
activate Model

Model --> Controller: 14. Return user data
deactivate Model
activate Controller

alt Login successful
    note right of Controller
        Set session data:
        - Store user info in session
        - Set login status
        - Redirect to admin dashboard
    end note

    Controller -> Browser: 15. redirect('administrator/home')
    activate Browser

    Browser -> Server: 16. GET /administrator/home
    activate Server
    deactivate Browser

    Server -> Router: 17. Route to Administrator controller home()
    activate Router
    deactivate Server

    Router -> Controller: 18. Call home() method
    activate Controller
    deactivate Router

    note right of Controller
        Load dashboard data:
        - User modules/permissions
        - System statistics
        - Recent activities
    end note

    Controller -> Model: 19. view_where('users',['username'=>$session_username])
    activate Model

    Model -> Database: 20. SELECT * FROM users\nWHERE username = '$session_username'
    activate Database
    deactivate Model

    Database --> Model: 21. Return user data
    deactivate Database
    activate Model

    Model --> Controller: 22. Return user data
    deactivate Model
    activate Controller

    Controller -> Browser: 23. Render dashboard template\n(template().'/administrator/home', $data)
    activate Browser

    Browser -> Administrator: 24. Display admin dashboard
    deactivate Browser

else Login failed
    note right of Controller
        Handle login failure:
        - Set error message
        - Regenerate captcha
        - Reload login form
    end note

    Controller -> Browser: 25. Render login template\nwith error message
    activate Browser

    Browser -> Administrator: 26. Display login form\nwith error message
    deactivate Browser
end

@enduml
